description: Dialectal rendering of man, as used in American Spanish.

entries.meaning: Alternative form of man (suggesting a Spanish accent)

description: From Middle English mang, mangis, imang, emang, variants of Middle English on mang, in mange, from Old English on ġemang. More at among.
From Middle English mangen, mængen, from Old English mængan, variant of mengan, menċġan (“to mix; mingle”). More at meng, ming.

verbs.description: mang (third-person singular simple present mangs, present participle manging, simple past and past participle manged)

description: Borrowed from Angloromani mong (“to beg”), from European Romani mang- (“to want, beg”). Compare Sanskrit mārg-, मार्ग् (“to seek, ask for”).

verbs.description: mang (third-person singular simple present mangs, present participle manging, simple past and past participle manged)

entries.meaning: (slang, dated, rare, transative, intransitive) To beg; to beg for money.
